TITLE: Retailers see a tough year ahead, so they're rolling out the recession playbook
SUMMARY: Retailers including Target, Macy's and Kroger previewed their strategies for a slowdown in recent earnings reports.

TITLE: Virgin Orbit pauses operations for a week, furloughs nearly entire staff as it seeks funding
SUMMARY: Virgin Orbit is furloughing nearly all its employees and pausing operations for a week as it looks for a funding lifeline.

TITLE: Airline stocks slide despite CEOs' upbeat demand outlook
SUMMARY: Pricy vacations have helped revive airline profits in recent months.

TITLE: Homebuilders say demand is rising, but they're concerned about banking fallout
SUMMARY: Homebuilder confidence rose in March for the third straight month, but sales expectations over the next six months fell.

TITLE: Norfolk Southern reaches new paid sick leave deal as it contends with derailment fallout
SUMMARY: Norfolk Southern said it reached a deal to offer up to seven paid sick days to members of the International Brotherhood of Boilermakers and Blacksmiths.

TITLE: Axiom unveils spacesuits for NASA's upcoming Artemis moon missions
SUMMARY: Axiom Space on Wednesday revealed a prototype of the lunar spacesuit that NASA plans to use on its Artemis missions to the moon.

TITLE: 3M fights a growing legal battle over combat-grade earplugs
SUMMARY: More than 200,000 military service members and veterans are suing 3M claiming its Combat Arms earplugs failed to protect them.

TITLE: Watch Jon Favreau talk streaming, storytelling and 'The Mandalorian'
SUMMARY: Jon Favreau, showrunner of "The Mandalorian," talks streaming, storytelling and crafting a new generation of Star Wars.

TITLE: Kellogg's snacking unit, which includes Cheez-It and Pringles, gets a new name: Kellanova
SUMMARY: Kellanova, which will include brands like Pringles and Cheez-Its, will retain the "K" stock ticker currently used by Kellogg.

TITLE: Diamond Sports, largest owner of regional sports networks, files for bankruptcy
SUMMARY: Diamond Sports has filed for bankruptcy protection with plans to eliminate more than $8 billion in debt.

TITLE: 'Rust' prosecutor steps down after challenge from Alec Baldwin's defense
SUMMARY: Baldwin's attorneys sought to disqualify the prosecutor, Andrea Reeb, because of her position as a state legislator.

TITLE: Mortgage demand rises despite volatile interest rates
SUMMARY: Demand for mortgages increased for the second straight week, despite some wide volatility in mortgage rates.

TITLE: Tyson Foods to lay off 1,700 workers, close two chicken plants
SUMMARY: In its latest quarter, Tyson said its chicken business underperformed expectations.

TITLE: Ohio sues Norfolk Southern over East Palestine derailment
SUMMARY: Ohio sued rail company Norfolk Southern over the derailment of a train carrying toxic materials in East Palestine last month

TITLE: Amazon shows off new satellite internet antennas as it takes on SpaceX's Starlink
SUMMARY: Amazon revealed a trio of satellite antennas, as the company prepares to take on SpaceX's Starlink with its Project Kuiper internet network.

TITLE: AMC plunges as investors approve reverse stock split, APE share conversion
SUMMARY: AMC investors voted to approve a reverse stock split and the conversion of APE shares into common company shares.

TITLE: Boeing sells 78 Dreamliner planes to Saudi airlines
SUMMARY: Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman announced the launch of a new airline, Riyadh Air, over the weekend.

TITLE: Michael Jordan's 'Last Dance' sneakers are going up for auction
SUMMARY: The Air Jordans are expected to be the most expensive pair of sneakers ever to appear at auction, estimated to sell for between $2 million and $4 million.

TITLE: Southwest Airlines vows to increase winter staffing and improve tech after holiday mess
SUMMARY: The carrier continues to expect a first-quarter loss because of the meltdown and now expects higher unit costs than previously forecast.

TITLE: Volkswagen announces five-year $193 billion investment plan as electrification gathers pace
SUMMARY: More than two thirds of Volkswagen's planned five-year investment will target "electrification and digitalization."

TITLE: Mortgage rates tumble in the wake of bank failures
SUMMARY: The average rate on the popular 30-year fixed mortgage dropped to 6.57% Monday, according to Mortgage News Daily.

TITLE: United shares tumble after airline forecasts first-quarter loss
SUMMARY: United Airlines forecast a first-quarter loss, citing weaker demand early in the year and higher costs.

TITLE: SpaceX says it will test Starlink's satellite-to-cell service with T-Mobile this year
SUMMARY: SpaceX plans to begin testing its Starlink satellite-to-cell service with T-Mobile "this year," an executive of Elon Musk's company said on Monday.

TITLE: Rivian is revisiting its exclusivity agreement with Amazon for EV delivery trucks
SUMMARY: Eliminating the exclusivity clause of the agreement would allow Rivian to court new customers as it works to ramp up production and seeks a cash infusion.

TITLE: Biden administration urges Congress to ban airlines from charging families to sit together
SUMMARY: The Biden administration has taken aim at add-on fees across the travel and entertainment industries.

TITLE: FAA clears Boeing to resume deliveries of 787 Dreamliners after weekslong pause
SUMMARY: Boeing on Friday said it has completed the required analysis on its 787 Dreamliners.

TITLE: Ford recalling 18 electric F-150 Lightning pickup trucks after battery fire
SUMMARY: Ford is recalling 18 F-150 Lightning pickups that have been identified as potentially having a battery cell defect that caused a truck to catch fire last month.

TITLE: The Oscar box office bump is shrinking
SUMMARY: The winner of the best picture award at this year's Oscars may not get a big box office bump in this streaming-dominated landscape.

TITLE: Betting on WWE matches? 'NFW!' say gaming operators and regulators
SUMMARY: Gaming operators and regulators smack down a reported effort by the WWE to enter the gambling fray.

TITLE: Luxury home sales plunge 45%, with Miami and the Hamptons hit hardest
SUMMARY: Tight supply and higher rates are pushing luxury home prices higher.
